textInverse` is in the list. Good. `border` is in list. Good.\n\nLet me verify all token names I use exist: text, textDim, textInverse, background, border, accent, success, warning, error, info, toolPending, toolRunning, toolResult, toolError, roleUser, roleAssistant, roleSystem, modeBadge.normal/plan/ultracode. Yes all listed.\n\nNow `theme.modeBadge[mode]` — I'm using token() instead, which is fine and preferred.\n\nLet me also handle the `depth` prop properly. The brief says \"Detect depth ONCE at module top, or accept an optional depth prop defaulting to it\". I'll do both: module-level DEPTH, and `depth ?? DEPTH`.\n\nNow about `useRef` import in PermissionPrompt — `import { useRef } from 'react'`.\n\nLet me also reconsider: the brief says PermissionPrompt \"call onDecision(d) exactly once\". My ref guard handles that. Good.\n\nLet me also reconsider the `useInput` — it's from 'ink'. Good.\n\nNow, one issue: in tests, when I `stdin.write('y')`, the useInput handler fires. But there might be timing — ink-testing-library is synchronous-ish. Should work.\n\nLet me also make sure `Static` items type — `<Static items={committed}>{(msg) => ...}</Static>`. The callback receives item and index. I use msg.id as key. Good.\n\nNow let me write the final document. Let me also double check the `Message` component — I reference `color` (role color) inside renderBlock. Let me restructure to pass it.\n\nLet me rewrite Message cleanly:\n\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { ReactElement } from 'react';\nimport type { Msg, Block } from '../core/reducer';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { ToolCallCard } from './ToolCallCard';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nfunction roleToken(role: Msg['role'], d: ColorDepth): string {\n  switch (role) {\n    case 'user': return token('roleUser', d);\n    case 'assistant': return token('roleAssistant', d);\n    case 'system': return token('roleSystem', d);\n    case 'tool': return token('textDim', d);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction BlockView({ block, msg, d }: { block: Block; msg: Msg; d: ColorDepth }): ReactElement {\n  switch (block.kind) {\n    case 'text':\n      return <Text color={roleToken(msg.role, d)}>{block.text}</Text>;\n    case 'tool': {\n      const tool = msg.toolSnapshot?.[block.toolCallId];\n      return tool\n        ? <ToolCallCard tool={tool} depth={d} />\n        : <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>[tool {block.toolCallId}]</Text>;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport interface MessageProps { msg: Msg; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function Message({ msg, depth }: MessageProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n      {msg.reasoning ? (\n        <Text color={token('textDim', d)} dimColor>thinking: {msg.reasoning}</Text>\n      ) : null}\n      {msg.blocks.map((block) => (\n        <BlockView key={block.id} block={block} msg={msg} d={d} />\n      ))}\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nGood. Exhaustive switch on block.kind.\n\nNow `dimColor` prop on Text — Ink 5 supports `dimColor`. Good.\n\nLet me finalize. I think we're ready. Let me write it all out.\n\nOne more: the test file needs to import JSX runtime? No. With react-jsx, no React import needed. But TypeScript needs to know about JSX. tsconfig handles. Fine.\n\nAlso for `render` returning `lastFrame()` possibly null — ink-testing-library types `lastFrame(): string | undefined`. So `expect(f).toContain(...)` — if f is undefined, toContain would fail. Let me assert non-null or use `f ?? ''`. Actually `expect(f).toContain(...)` where f is `string | undefined` — vitest's toContain accepts. But TS might complain. Let me cast: `const f = lastFrame() ?? '';`. Safer.\n\nLet me do that in tests.\n\nAlso `stdin.write` — ink-testing-library provides `stdin` with `write` method. Good.\n\nNow writing final.\n\nFor the `selectStatusLine` — I need to ensure contextFraction is a number. With my state having tokens in:100 out:50 and no maxContext, the selector computes fraction. I don't know exact logic but it should produce a number 0..1. The test just checks for a bar char. Fine.\n\nLet me write everything now.","reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":"Let me carefully plan out all the files I need to write.\n\n1. `src/ui/Transcript.tsx` - wraps Static, renders Message for each committed\n2. `src/ui/Message.tsx` - role-tinted, renders blocks, reasoning\n3. `src/ui/StreamingMessage.tsx` - like Message for live, with Spinner\n4. `src/ui/ToolCallCard.tsx` - bordered box, status color, name, summary\n5. `src/ui/ModeBadge.tsx` - mode badge with background tint\n6. `src/ui/StatusLine.tsx` - model, cwd, tokens, context bar, mode, statusText\n7. `src/ui/InputBox.tsx` - TextInput wrapper\n8. `src/ui/SlashPalette.tsx` - list commands, highlight selected\n9. `src/ui/ModelPicker.tsx` - list models, highlight selected\n10. `src/ui/PermissionPrompt.tsx` - show tool, risk, useInput for decisions\n11. `src/ui/OverlayHost.tsx` - switch on overlay\n12. `src/ui/tests/components.test.tsx` - tests\n\nLet me think about the theme API. `token(name, depth?)` returns a string ready for `<Text color={...}>`. `theme.modeBadge[mode]` is a hex presumably. `downsample(hex, depth)`.\n\nFor ModeBadge, \"background-ish tint; use textInverse for the text on the badge\". Ink Text has `backgroundColor` prop. So `<Text backgroundColor={token('modeBadge.'+mode)} color={token('textInverse')}>`.\n\nLet me check the token names: `modeBadge.normal | modeBadge.plan | modeBadge.ultracode`. Good.\n\nFor PermissionDecision type from events: `'allow-once'|'deny'|'always-allow-pattern'|'dangerous-bypass'`. RiskLevel: probably `'safe'|'risky'|'dangerous'` — let me assume. Actually I should be careful. The brief says \"safe→success/neutral, risky→warning, dangerous→error\". So RiskLevel = 'safe'|'risky'|'dangerous'. I'll import the type and do exhaustive switch.\n\nFor ModelEntry from catalog - I don't know its shape exactly. The brief says \"list models (label + id), highlight selectedId\". So ModelEntry has at least `id` and `label`. Let me assume `{ id: string; label: string; ... }`. I'll use `m.id` and `m.label`.\n\nLet me write each file.\n\n### theme.ts usage\n```ts\nimport { token, theme, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n```\n\nActually I'll accept `depth?` prop defaulting to module-level DEPTH.\n\nLet me write a small helper for depth: `const d = depth ?? DEPTH`.\n\n### Transcript.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Static } from 'ink';\nimport type { Msg } from '../core/reducer';\nimport type { ColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { detectColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { Message } from './Message';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface TranscriptProps { committed: Msg[]; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function Transcript({ committed, depth }: TranscriptProps): React.ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Static items={committed}>\n      {(msg) => <Message key={msg.id} msg={msg} depth={d} />}\n    </Static>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nWait, React.ReactElement - need to import type. Actually with react-jsx I don't need to import React but for types I need `import type { ReactElement } from 'react'` or use `JSX.Element`. Let me use `React.ReactElement` — but React isn't imported. I'll `import type { ReactElement } from 'react'`.\n\nActually the brief says \"import named hooks\" from react. For types I can `import type { ReactElement } from 'react'`.\n\n### Message.tsx\nRole tinting: roleUser/roleAssistant/roleSystem tokens. Also role 'tool' — but roles are 'user'|'assistant'|'tool'|'system'. The brief mentions roleUser/roleAssistant/roleSystem tokens but not roleTool. For 'tool' role I'll use textDim or toolResult. Let me handle exhaustively: user→roleUser, assistant→roleAssistant, system→roleSystem, tool→textDim (or toolResult). \n\nBlocks: text → `<Text>`; tool → ToolCallCard if snapshot present, else maybe nothing/dim.\n\nReasoning: dim, \"thinking\" label.\n\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { Msg, Block, ToolState } from '../core/reducer';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { ToolCallCard } from './ToolCallCard';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nfunction roleToken(role: Msg['role'], depth: ColorDepth): string {\n  switch (role) {\n    case 'user': return token('roleUser', depth);\n    case 'assistant': return token('roleAssistant', depth);\n    case 'system': return token('roleSystem', depth);\n    case 'tool': return token('textDim', depth);\n  }\n}\n\nexport interface MessageProps { msg: Msg; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function Message({ msg, depth }: MessageProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  const color = roleToken(msg.role, d);\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n      {msg.reasoning ? (\n        <Box>\n          <Text color={token('textDim', d)} dimColor>thinking: {msg.reasoning}</Text>\n        </Box>\n      ) : null}\n      <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n        {msg.blocks.map((block) => renderBlock(block, msg, d))}\n      </Box>\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction renderBlock(block: Block, msg: Msg, d: ColorDepth): ReactElement {\n  switch (block.kind) {\n    case 'text':\n      return <Text key={block.id} color={color}>{block.text}</Text>;  // hmm color scoping\n    case 'tool': {\n      const tool = msg.toolSnapshot?.[block.toolCallId];\n      return tool ? <ToolCallCard key={block.id} tool={tool} depth={d} /> : <Text key={block.id} color={token('textDim', d)}>[tool {block.toolCallId}]</Text>;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nHmm, color variable scoping in renderBlock. Let me restructure. Actually let me just inline.\n\nLet me reconsider — I want role color on text blocks. Let me pass color in.\n\n### StreamingMessage.tsx\nSame as Message but for live, with Spinner while streaming (msg.done === false).\n\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport { Spinner } from 'ink-spinner';\nimport type { Msg } from '../core/reducer';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { Message } from './Message';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface StreamingMessageProps { live: Msg | null; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function StreamingMessage({ live, depth }: StreamingMessageProps): ReactElement | null {\n  if (!live) return null;\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n      <Message msg={live} depth={d} />\n      {!live.done ? <Box><Spinner /><Text> </Text></Box> : null}\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nWait Spinner needs a type prop? ink-spinner default is fine. Actually `Spinner` has default type 'dots'. OK.\n\nBut returning `null` from a component — ReactElement | null. Fine.\n\n### ToolCallCard.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { ToolState } from '../core/reducer';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nfunction statusToken(status: ToolState['status'], d: ColorDepth): string {\n  switch (status) {\n    case 'pending': return token('toolPending', d);\n    case 'running': return token('toolRunning', d);\n    case 'result': return token('toolResult', d);\n    case 'error': return token('toolError', d);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction statusGlyph(status: ToolState['status']): string {\n  switch (status) {\n    case 'pending': return '○';\n    case 'running': return '◐';\n    case 'result': return '●';\n    case 'error': return '✖';\n  }\n}\n\nfunction summarize(v: unknown): string {\n  if (v === undefined || v === null) return '';\n  if (typeof v === 'string') return v;\n  try { return JSON.stringify(v); } catch { return String(v); }\n}\n\nexport interface ToolCallCardProps { tool: ToolState; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function ToolCallCard({ tool, depth }: ToolCallCardProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  const color = statusToken(tool.status, d);\n  return (\n    <Box borderStyle=\"round\" borderColor={color} flexDirection=\"column\" paddingLeft={1} paddingRight={1}>\n      <Box>\n        <Text color={color}>{statusGlyph(tool.status)} </Text>\n        <Text color={token('text', d)} bold>{tool.name}</Text>\n        <Text color={token('textDim', d)}> [{tool.status}]</Text>\n      </Box>\n      {tool.status === 'result' && tool.result !== undefined ? (\n        <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>{summarize(tool.result)}</Text>\n      ) : null}\n      {tool.status === 'error' && tool.error ? (\n        <Text color={token('error', d)}>{tool.error}</Text>\n      ) : null}\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### ModeBadge.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { State } from '../core/reducer';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface ModeBadgeProps { mode: State['mode']; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function ModeBadge({ mode, depth }: ModeBadgeProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  const bg = token(`modeBadge.${mode}` as any, d);  // no any!\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nI can't use `as any`. The FlatTokenName type is `keyof Theme (minus modeBadge) | 'modeBadge.normal' | ...`. So I need to construct the token name properly. Let me do a switch:\n\n```tsx\nfunction modeToken(mode: State['mode'], d: ColorDepth): string {\n  switch (mode) {\n    case 'normal': return token('modeBadge.normal', d);\n    case 'plan': return token('modeBadge.plan', d);\n    case 'ultracode': return token('modeBadge.ultracode', d);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nGood, exhaustive.\n\n```tsx\nexport function ModeBadge({ mode, depth }: ModeBadgeProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  const bg = modeToken(mode, d);\n  return (\n    <Text backgroundColor={bg} color={token('textInverse', d)}> {mode.toUpperCase()} </Text>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### StatusLine.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { StatusLineState } from '../core/selectors';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\nimport { ModeBadge } from './ModeBadge';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nfunction contextBar(frac: number, d: ColorDepth): ReactElement {\n  const clamped = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, frac));\n  const width = 10;\n  const filled = Math.round(clamped * width);\n  const empty = width - filled;\n  return (\n    <Text>\n      <Text color={token('accent', d)}>{'█'.repeat(filled)}</Text>\n      <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>{'░'.repeat(empty)}</Text>\n    </Text>\n  );\n}\n\nexport interface StatusLineProps { status: StatusLineState; depth?: ColorDepth }\n\nexport function StatusLine({ status, depth }: StatusLineProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n      <Box gap={1}>\n        <Text color={token('accent', d)} bold>{status.model}</Text>\n        <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>{status.cwd}</Text>\n        <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>tok:{status.tokens.total}</Text>\n        {contextBar(status.contextFraction, d)}\n        <ModeBadge mode={status.mode} depth={d} />\n      </Box>\n      <Box>\n        <Text color={token('text', d)}>{status.statusText}</Text>\n      </Box>\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### InputBox.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport TextInput from 'ink-text-input';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface InputBoxProps { value: string; onChange:(v:string)=>void; onSubmit:(v:string)=>void; placeholder?:string; depth?:ColorDepth }\n\nexport function InputBox({ value, onChange, onSubmit, placeholder, depth }: InputBoxProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box>\n      <Text color={token('accent', d)}>❯ </Text>\n      <TextInput value={value} onChange={onChange} onSubmit={onSubmit} placeholder={placeholder ?? ''} />\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nink-text-input default export. Good.\n\n### SlashPalette.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface SlashPaletteProps { commands: Array<{ name:string; description:string }>; selectedIndex?:number; depth?:ColorDepth }\n\nexport function SlashPalette({ commands, selectedIndex = 0, depth }: SlashPaletteProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\" borderStyle=\"round\" borderColor={token('border', d)} paddingX={1}>\n      {commands.map((c, i) => {\n        const selected = i === selectedIndex;\n        return (\n          <Box key={c.name} gap={1}>\n            <Text color={selected ? token('accent', d) : token('textDim', d)}>{selected ? '▸' : ' '}</Text>\n            <Text color={selected ? token('accent', d) : token('text', d)} bold={selected}>/{c.name}</Text>\n            <Text color={token('textDim', d)}>{c.description}</Text>\n          </Box>\n        );\n      })}\n    </Box>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### ModelPicker.tsx\n```tsx\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\nimport type { ModelEntry } from '../services/catalog';\nimport { token, detectColorDepth, type ColorDepth } from './theme';\n\nconst DEPTH = detectColorDepth();\n\nexport interface ModelPickerProps { models: ReadonlyArray<ModelEntry>; selectedId?:string; depth?:ColorDepth }\n\nexport function ModelPicker({ models, selectedId, depth }: ModelPickerProps): ReactElement {\n  const d = depth ?? DEPTH;\n  return (\n    <Box flexDirection=\"column\" borderStyle=\"round\" borderColor={token('border', d)} paddingX={1}>\n      {models.map((m) => {\n        const selected = m.id === selectedId;\n        return (\n          <Box key={m.id} gap={1}>\n            <Text color={selected ? token('accent', d) : token('textDim', d)}>{selected ? '▸' : ' '}</Text>\n            <Text color={selected ? token('accent', d) : token('text', d)} bold={selected}>{m.label}</Text>\n            <Text c